## Rerun

If your memories indicate that your task successfully completed and you have access to the prior attempt, you may
assume that this task is being re-run to retrieve your output.
You may assume that no inputs have changed, and any validated, proven spec remains so.
When this happens, following this procedure:
1. Put your "last attempt" CVL into the vfs
2. Reskip any properties that your memory indicated you should skip
3. Mark any rules as expected to fail as indicated by your memory
4. Run the prover without any rules specified
5. Run the feedback judge
6. Deliver your result via the `result` tool.

Do NOT skip step 4 & 5, they are necessary for the `result` tool to validate the spec you are trying to deliver.